repmat          package:multivariateAnomaly          R Documentation

_R_e_p_l_i_c_a_t_e _m_a_t_r_i_x.

_D_e_s_c_r_i_p_t_i_o_n:

     Analogous to the repmat function in matlab. A = repmat(B, m, n)
     creates a new matrix A having m * n tiling of B. The size of the
     matrix A will be [nrow(B) * m, ncol(B) * n]

_U_s_a_g_e:

     repmat(B, m, n)

_A_r_g_u_m_e_n_t_s:

       B: The input matrix that has to be replicated. 

       m: Number of tilings along the row. 

       n: Number of tilings along the column. 

_A_u_t_h_o_r(_s):

     Sriram Lakshminarasimhan

_E_x_a_m_p_l_e_s:

     B <- matrix(c(1:9), nrow=3)
     B
     A <- repmat(B, 2, 3)
     A

